  "response": "\"Ight\" is a casual, shortened version of \"alright\" or \"all right.\" It's commonly used in text messages, online chats, and informal conversation, especially among younger people. It can mean:\n\n1. Okay\n2. Sounds good\n3. Fine\n4. I agree\n\nFor example:\n- \"Want to meet up later?\" \"Ight\"\n- \"I'll pick you up at 8.\" \"Ight\"",
